	   SHORT="xalf provides feedback when starting X11 applications"
cat << EOF
Xalf is a small utility to provide feedback when starting X11
applications. Feedback can be given via four different indicators: an 
invisible window (to be used in conjunction with a task pager like
GNOME's tasklist_applet or KDE's Taskbar), an generic splashscreen,
an hourglass attached to the mouse cursor, or an animated star.
EOF
